SVM Kernel Comparison Lab: Using the make_moons and make_circles synthetic
datasets, train SVM with Linear, Polynomial (degree 2 and 3), and RBF kernels and
visualise the decision boundary for each. Then switch to the Breast Cancer dataset,
apply StandardScaler, and train SVC with the RBF kernel. Use GridSearchCV to tune C
and gamma over a grid and report the best parameters. Plot the heatmap of GridSearch
scores (C vs gamma). Compare SVM against Logistic Regression, KNN, and Random
Forest using accuracy, F1, and AUC-ROC. Print a final model comparison table across
all five classifiers covered this week.
